ðŸ”¹ 3. Networking Devices
15. What is a hub?
A hub sends data to all devices in the network.
16. What is a switch?
A switch sends data only to the intended device using MAC address.
17. What is a router?
A router connects different networks and forwards data packets.
18. What is a firewall?
A firewall protects a network by filtering traffic.
19. What is NAT?
NAT converts private IP to public IP for internet access.
20. What is VLAN?
VLAN logically divides a network into smaller networks.
